*** The Exact Steps in Which a Tote is Closed in WMx ***

WMX Contaner Build converts SSCC into CASEID via issuing 'GET' request to 'http://api.cqrs.wmxp008.wmx.sc.xpo.com/queryservice/order/3030323733313239383234383034363130353038/case' where SSCC is spliced with the number 3 in front of every digit.
i.e. SSCC 00273129824804610508 becomes 3030323733313239383234383034363130353038 and is sent as seen above. 
Then CASEID is sent back as a response.

THEN...

We send the CASEID as another 'GET' request *also* spliced with the number 3 infront of every digit. i.e. CASEID: 0011540877
is sent as 'http://api.outbound.wmxp008.wmx.sc.xpo.com/container/opencontainersingle/30303131353430383737/' 
This gives us back the CONTAINERKEY that has been assigned to the tote.

THEN...

We take the CONTAINERKEY and *once again* splice it with the number 3 infront of every digit. i.e. with CONTAINERKEY 0002392596, We send it in the form of 'http://api.cqrs.wmxp008.wmx.sc.xpo.com/queryservice/containership/30303032333932353936'
This gives us pretty much all the data pertaining to the container.

THEN...

We send out 'http://api.cqrs.wmxp008.wmx.sc.xpo.com/queryservice/containershipdetailsbycontainerkey/30303032333932353936' where we are passing in a spliced CONTAINERKEY but this request fails. So...

THEN...

We send out a 'PUT' request in the form of 'http://api.outbound.wmxp008.wmx.sc.xpo.com/container/addcasesingle/30303032333932353936/30303131353430383737/' where we are sending spliced CONTAINERKEY followed by spliced CASEID. The payload is an empty JSON, i.e. '{}' and the server does not respond with any information.

THEN...

We send out the 'http://api.cqrs.wmxp008.wmx.sc.xpo.com/queryservice/containership/30303032333932353936' 'GET' request *again*, except this time, the response tells us the calculated weight of the container and that its status went from '101' to '151'.

THEN...

I don't know if order matters, but *in rough order* 
http://api.cqrs.wmxp008.wmx.sc.xpo.com/queryservice/containership/30303032333932353936
This request returns the exact values that get sent to the iscontainerdirty request 

http://api.cqrs.wmxp008.wmx.sc.xpo.com/queryservice/containershipdetailsbycontainerkey/30303032333932353936

http://api.cqrs.wmxp008.wmx.sc.xpo.com/queryservice/configbyconfigid/all/434e545041434b4147455459504557495448434152544f4e54595045

(((( At this point, the user presses the 'process' button in the interface, commencing the action of closing the tote ))))

'PUT' http://api.outbound.wmxp008.wmx.sc.xpo.com/container/iscontainerdirty
the payload here
